58 if (dbg_session) \

60 "%s: " dbg_fmt, \
61 __func__, ##arg); \
62 } while (0);

64#define ISCSI_DBG_TRANS_CONN(_conn, dbg_fmt, arg...) \
65 do { \
66 if (dbg_conn) \
67 iscsi_cls_conn_printk(KERN_INFO, _conn, \
68 "%s: " dbg_fmt, \
69 __func__, ##arg); \
70 } while (0);

168show_ep_handle(struct device *dev, struct device_attribute *attr, char *buf)

175static struct attribute *iscsi_endpoint_attrs[] = {

178};

180static struct attribute_group iscsi_endpoint_group = {
181 .attrs = iscsi_endpoint_attrs,
182};

184#define ISCSI_MAX_EPID -1
185
186static int iscsi_match_epid(struct device *dev, const void *data)
187{
188 struct iscsi_endpoint *ep = iscsi_dev_to_endpoint(dev);
189 const uint64_t *epid = data;
190
191 return *epid == ep->id;
192}
193
194struct iscsi_endpoint *
195iscsi_create_endpoint(int dd_size)
196{
197 struct device *dev;
198 struct iscsi_endpoint *ep;
199 uint64_t id;
200 int err;
201
202 for (id = 1; id < ISCSI_MAX_EPID; id++) {
203 dev = class_find_device(&iscsi_endpoint_class, NULL, &id,
204 iscsi_match_epid);
205 if (!dev)
206 break;
207 else
208 put_device(dev);
209 }
210 if (id == ISCSI_MAX_EPID) {
211 printk(KERN_ERR "Too many connections. Max supported %u\n",
212 ISCSI_MAX_EPID - 1);
213 return NULL;
214 }
215
216 ep = kzalloc(sizeof(*ep) + dd_size, GFP_KERNEL);
217 if (!ep)
218 return NULL;
219
220 ep->id = id;
221 ep->dev.class = &iscsi_endpoint_class;
222 dev_set_name(&ep->dev, "ep-%llu", (unsigned long long) id);
223 err = device_register(&ep->dev);
224 if (err)
225 goto free_ep;
226
227 err = sysfs_create_group(&ep->dev.kobj, &iscsi_endpoint_group);
228 if (err)
229 goto unregister_dev;
230
231 if (dd_size)
232 ep->dd_data = &ep[1];
233 return ep;
234
235unregister_dev:
236 device_unregister(&ep->dev);
237 return NULL;
238
239free_ep:
240 kfree(ep);
241 return NULL;
242}
243EXPORT_SYMBOL_GPL(iscsi_create_endpoint);
244
245void iscsi_destroy_endpoint(struct iscsi_endpoint *ep)
246{
247 sysfs_remove_group(&ep->dev.kobj, &iscsi_endpoint_group);
248 device_unregister(&ep->dev);
249}
250EXPORT_SYMBOL_GPL(iscsi_destroy_endpoint);
251
252struct iscsi_endpoint *iscsi_lookup_endpoint(u64 handle)
253{
254 struct iscsi_endpoint *ep;
255 struct device *dev;
256
257 dev = class_find_device(&iscsi_endpoint_class, NULL, &handle,
258 iscsi_match_epid);
259 if (!dev)
260 return NULL;
261
262 ep = iscsi_dev_to_endpoint(dev);
263 /*
264 * we can drop this now because the interface will prevent
265 * removals and lookups from racing.
266 */
267 put_device(dev);
268 return ep;
269}
270EXPORT_SYMBOL_GPL(iscsi_lookup_endpoint);

276static void iscsi_iface_release(struct device *dev)
277{
278 struct iscsi_iface *iface = iscsi_dev_to_iface(dev);
279 struct device *parent = iface->dev.parent;
280
281 kfree(iface);
282 put_device(parent);
283}

418static umode_t iscsi_iface_attr_is_visible(struct kobject *kobj,
419 struct attribute *attr, int i)
420{
421 struct device *dev = container_of(kobj, struct device, kobj);
422 struct iscsi_iface *iface = iscsi_dev_to_iface(dev);
423 struct iscsi_transport *t = iface->transport;
424 int param;
425 int param_type;
426
427 if (attr == &dev_attr_iface_enabled.attr)
428 param = ISCSI_NET_PARAM_IFACE_ENABLE;
429 else if (attr == &dev_attr_iface_vlan_id.attr)
430 param = ISCSI_NET_PARAM_VLAN_ID;
431 else if (attr == &dev_attr_iface_vlan_priority.attr)
432 param = ISCSI_NET_PARAM_VLAN_PRIORITY;
433 else if (attr == &dev_attr_iface_vlan_enabled.attr)
434 param = ISCSI_NET_PARAM_VLAN_ENABLED;
435 else if (attr == &dev_attr_iface_mtu.attr)
436 param = ISCSI_NET_PARAM_MTU;
437 else if (attr == &dev_attr_iface_port.attr)
438 param = ISCSI_NET_PARAM_PORT;
439 else if (attr == &dev_attr_iface_ipaddress_state.attr)
440 param = ISCSI_NET_PARAM_IPADDR_STATE;
441 else if (attr == &dev_attr_iface_delayed_ack_en.attr)
442 param = ISCSI_NET_PARAM_DELAYED_ACK_EN;
443 else if (attr == &dev_attr_iface_tcp_nagle_disable.attr)
444 param = ISCSI_NET_PARAM_TCP_NAGLE_DISABLE;
445 else if (attr == &dev_attr_iface_tcp_wsf_disable.attr)
446 param = ISCSI_NET_PARAM_TCP_WSF_DISABLE;
447 else if (attr == &dev_attr_iface_tcp_wsf.attr)
448 param = ISCSI_NET_PARAM_TCP_WSF;
449 else if (attr == &dev_attr_iface_tcp_timer_scale.attr)
450 param = ISCSI_NET_PARAM_TCP_TIMER_SCALE;
451 else if (attr == &dev_attr_iface_tcp_timestamp_en.attr)
452 param = ISCSI_NET_PARAM_TCP_TIMESTAMP_EN;
453 else if (attr == &dev_attr_iface_cache_id.attr)
454 param = ISCSI_NET_PARAM_CACHE_ID;
455 else if (attr == &dev_attr_iface_redirect_en.attr)
456 param = ISCSI_NET_PARAM_REDIRECT_EN;
457 else if (attr == &dev_attr_iface_def_taskmgmt_tmo.attr)
458 param = ISCSI_IFACE_PARAM_DEF_TASKMGMT_TMO;
459 else if (attr == &dev_attr_iface_header_digest.attr)
460 param = ISCSI_IFACE_PARAM_HDRDGST_EN;
461 else if (attr == &dev_attr_iface_data_digest.attr)
462 param = ISCSI_IFACE_PARAM_DATADGST_EN;
463 else if (attr == &dev_attr_iface_immediate_data.attr)
464 param = ISCSI_IFACE_PARAM_IMM_DATA_EN;
465 else if (attr == &dev_attr_iface_initial_r2t.attr)
466 param = ISCSI_IFACE_PARAM_INITIAL_R2T_EN;
467 else if (attr == &dev_attr_iface_data_seq_in_order.attr)
468 param = ISCSI_IFACE_PARAM_DATASEQ_INORDER_EN;
469 else if (attr == &dev_attr_iface_data_pdu_in_order.attr)
470 param = ISCSI_IFACE_PARAM_PDU_INORDER_EN;
471 else if (attr == &dev_attr_iface_erl.attr)
472 param = ISCSI_IFACE_PARAM_ERL;
473 else if (attr == &dev_attr_iface_max_recv_dlength.attr)
474 param = ISCSI_IFACE_PARAM_MAX_RECV_DLENGTH;
475 else if (attr == &dev_attr_iface_first_burst_len.attr)
476 param = ISCSI_IFACE_PARAM_FIRST_BURST;
477 else if (attr == &dev_attr_iface_max_outstanding_r2t.attr)
478 param = ISCSI_IFACE_PARAM_MAX_R2T;
479 else if (attr == &dev_attr_iface_max_burst_len.attr)
480 param = ISCSI_IFACE_PARAM_MAX_BURST;
481 else if (attr == &dev_attr_iface_chap_auth.attr)
482 param = ISCSI_IFACE_PARAM_CHAP_AUTH_EN;
483 else if (attr == &dev_attr_iface_bidi_chap.attr)
484 param = ISCSI_IFACE_PARAM_BIDI_CHAP_EN;
485 else if (attr == &dev_attr_iface_discovery_auth_optional.attr)
486 param = ISCSI_IFACE_PARAM_DISCOVERY_AUTH_OPTIONAL;
487 else if (attr == &dev_attr_iface_discovery_logout.attr)
488 param = ISCSI_IFACE_PARAM_DISCOVERY_LOGOUT_EN;
489 else if (attr == &dev_attr_iface_strict_login_comp_en.attr)
490 param = ISCSI_IFACE_PARAM_STRICT_LOGIN_COMP_EN;
491 else if (attr == &dev_attr_iface_initiator_name.attr)
492 param = ISCSI_IFACE_PARAM_INITIATOR_NAME;
493 else if (iface->iface_type == ISCSI_IFACE_TYPE_IPV4) {
494 if (attr == &dev_attr_ipv4_iface_ipaddress.attr)

504 param = ISCSI_NET_PARAM_IPV4_DHCP_DNS_ADDR_EN;
505 else if (attr ==
506 &dev_attr_ipv4_iface_dhcp_slp_da_info_en.attr)
507 param = ISCSI_NET_PARAM_IPV4_DHCP_SLP_DA_EN;
508 else if (attr == &dev_attr_ipv4_iface_tos_en.attr)
509 param = ISCSI_NET_PARAM_IPV4_TOS_EN;

514 else if (attr ==

516 param = ISCSI_NET_PARAM_IPV4_DHCP_ALT_CLIENT_ID_EN;
517 else if (attr == &dev_attr_ipv4_iface_dhcp_alt_client_id.attr)
518 param = ISCSI_NET_PARAM_IPV4_DHCP_ALT_CLIENT_ID;
519 else if (attr ==
520 &dev_attr_ipv4_iface_dhcp_req_vendor_id_en.attr)
521 param = ISCSI_NET_PARAM_IPV4_DHCP_REQ_VENDOR_ID_EN;
522 else if (attr ==
523 &dev_attr_ipv4_iface_dhcp_use_vendor_id_en.attr)

536 else if (attr == &dev_attr_ipv4_iface_ttl.attr)
537 param = ISCSI_NET_PARAM_IPV4_TTL;
538 else
539 return 0;
540 } else if (iface->iface_type == ISCSI_IFACE_TYPE_IPV6) {
541 if (attr == &dev_attr_ipv6_iface_ipaddress.attr)
542 param = ISCSI_NET_PARAM_IPV6_ADDR;
543 else if (attr == &dev_attr_ipv6_iface_link_local_addr.attr)

545 else if (attr == &dev_attr_ipv6_iface_router_addr.attr)

549 else if (attr == &dev_attr_ipv6_iface_link_local_autocfg.attr)
550 param = ISCSI_NET_PARAM_IPV6_LINKLOCAL_AUTOCFG;
551 else if (attr == &dev_attr_ipv6_iface_link_local_state.attr)
552 param = ISCSI_NET_PARAM_IPV6_LINKLOCAL_STATE;
553 else if (attr == &dev_attr_ipv6_iface_router_state.attr)
554 param = ISCSI_NET_PARAM_IPV6_ROUTER_STATE;
555 else if (attr ==
556 &dev_attr_ipv6_iface_grat_neighbor_adv_en.attr)
557 param = ISCSI_NET_PARAM_IPV6_GRAT_NEIGHBOR_ADV_EN;
558 else if (attr == &dev_attr_ipv6_iface_mld_en.attr)
559 param = ISCSI_NET_PARAM_IPV6_MLD_EN;
560 else if (attr == &dev_attr_ipv6_iface_flow_label.attr)
561 param = ISCSI_NET_PARAM_IPV6_FLOW_LABEL;
562 else if (attr == &dev_attr_ipv6_iface_traffic_class.attr)
563 param = ISCSI_NET_PARAM_IPV6_TRAFFIC_CLASS;
564 else if (attr == &dev_attr_ipv6_iface_hop_limit.attr)
565 param = ISCSI_NET_PARAM_IPV6_HOP_LIMIT;
566 else if (attr == &dev_attr_ipv6_iface_nd_reachable_tmo.attr)
567 param = ISCSI_NET_PARAM_IPV6_ND_REACHABLE_TMO;
568 else if (attr == &dev_attr_ipv6_iface_nd_rexmit_time.attr)
569 param = ISCSI_NET_PARAM_IPV6_ND_REXMIT_TIME;
570 else if (attr == &dev_attr_ipv6_iface_nd_stale_tmo.attr)
571 param = ISCSI_NET_PARAM_IPV6_ND_STALE_TMO;
572 else if (attr == &dev_attr_ipv6_iface_dup_addr_detect_cnt.attr)
573 param = ISCSI_NET_PARAM_IPV6_DUP_ADDR_DETECT_CNT;
574 else if (attr == &dev_attr_ipv6_iface_router_adv_link_mtu.attr)
575 param = ISCSI_NET_PARAM_IPV6_RTR_ADV_LINK_MTU;
576 else
577 return 0;
578 } else {
579 WARN_ONCE(1, "Invalid iface attr");
580 return 0;
581 }
582
583 switch (param) {
584 case ISCSI_IFACE_PARAM_DEF_TASKMGMT_TMO:
585 case ISCSI_IFACE_PARAM_HDRDGST_EN:
586 case ISCSI_IFACE_PARAM_DATADGST_EN:
587 case ISCSI_IFACE_PARAM_IMM_DATA_EN:
588 case ISCSI_IFACE_PARAM_INITIAL_R2T_EN:
589 case ISCSI_IFACE_PARAM_DATASEQ_INORDER_EN:
590 case ISCSI_IFACE_PARAM_PDU_INORDER_EN:
591 case ISCSI_IFACE_PARAM_ERL:
592 case ISCSI_IFACE_PARAM_MAX_RECV_DLENGTH:
593 case ISCSI_IFACE_PARAM_FIRST_BURST:
594 case ISCSI_IFACE_PARAM_MAX_R2T:
595 case ISCSI_IFACE_PARAM_MAX_BURST:
596 case ISCSI_IFACE_PARAM_CHAP_AUTH_EN:
597 case ISCSI_IFACE_PARAM_BIDI_CHAP_EN:
598 case ISCSI_IFACE_PARAM_DISCOVERY_AUTH_OPTIONAL:
599 case ISCSI_IFACE_PARAM_DISCOVERY_LOGOUT_EN:
600 case ISCSI_IFACE_PARAM_STRICT_LOGIN_COMP_EN:
601 case ISCSI_IFACE_PARAM_INITIATOR_NAME:
602 param_type = ISCSI_IFACE_PARAM;
603 break;
604 default:
605 param_type = ISCSI_NET_PARAM;
606 }
607
608 return t->attr_is_visible(param_type, param);
609}

688/* convert iscsi_ipaddress_state values to ascii string name */
689static const struct {
690 enum iscsi_ipaddress_state value;
691 char *name;
692} iscsi_ipaddress_state_names[] = {
693 {ISCSI_IPDDRESS_STATE_UNCONFIGURED, "Unconfigured" },
694 {ISCSI_IPDDRESS_STATE_ACQUIRING, "Acquiring" },
695 {ISCSI_IPDDRESS_STATE_TENTATIVE, "Tentative" },
696 {ISCSI_IPDDRESS_STATE_VALID, "Valid" },
697 {ISCSI_IPDDRESS_STATE_DISABLING, "Disabling" },
698 {ISCSI_IPDDRESS_STATE_INVALID, "Invalid" },
699 {ISCSI_IPDDRESS_STATE_DEPRECATED, "Deprecated" },
700};
701
702char *iscsi_get_ipaddress_state_name(enum iscsi_ipaddress_state port_state)
703{
704 int i;
705 char *state = NULL;
706
707 for (i = 0; i < ARRAY_SIZE(iscsi_ipaddress_state_names); i++) {
708 if (iscsi_ipaddress_state_names[i].value == port_state) {
709 state = iscsi_ipaddress_state_names[i].name;
710 break;
711 }
712 }
713 return state;
714}
715EXPORT_SYMBOL_GPL(iscsi_get_ipaddress_state_name);

722 {ISCSI_ROUTER_STATE_UNKNOWN, "Unknown" },
723 {ISCSI_ROUTER_STATE_ADVERTISED, "Advertised" },

743struct iscsi_iface *
744iscsi_create_iface(struct Scsi_Host *shost, struct iscsi_transport *transport,
745 uint32_t iface_type, uint32_t iface_num, int dd_size)
746{
747 struct iscsi_iface *iface;
748 int err;
749
750 iface = kzalloc(sizeof(*iface) + dd_size, GFP_KERNEL);
751 if (!iface)
752 return NULL;
753
754 iface->transport = transport;
755 iface->iface_type = iface_type;
756 iface->iface_num = iface_num;
757 iface->dev.release = iscsi_iface_release;
758 iface->dev.class = &iscsi_iface_class;
759 /* parent reference released in iscsi_iface_release */
760 iface->dev.parent = get_device(&shost->shost_gendev);
761 if (iface_type == ISCSI_IFACE_TYPE_IPV4)
762 dev_set_name(&iface->dev, "ipv4-iface-%u-%u", shost->host_no,
763 iface_num);
764 else
765 dev_set_name(&iface->dev, "ipv6-iface-%u-%u", shost->host_no,
766 iface_num);
767
768 err = device_register(&iface->dev);
769 if (err)
770 goto free_iface;
771
772 err = sysfs_create_group(&iface->dev.kobj, &iscsi_iface_group);
773 if (err)
774 goto unreg_iface;
775
776 if (dd_size)
777 iface->dd_data = &iface[1];
778 return iface;
779
780unreg_iface:
781 device_unregister(&iface->dev);
782 return NULL;
783
784free_iface:
785 put_device(iface->dev.parent);
786 kfree(iface);
787 return NULL;
788}
789EXPORT_SYMBOL_GPL(iscsi_create_iface);
790
791void iscsi_destroy_iface(struct iscsi_iface *iface)
792{
793 sysfs_remove_group(&iface->dev.kobj, &iscsi_iface_group);
794 device_unregister(&iface->dev);
795}
796EXPORT_SYMBOL_GPL(iscsi_destroy_iface);

907static umode_t iscsi_flashnode_sess_attr_is_visible(struct kobject *kobj,
908 struct attribute *attr,
909 int i)
910{
911 struct device *dev = container_of(kobj, struct device, kobj);
912 struct iscsi_bus_flash_session *fnode_sess =
913 iscsi_dev_to_flash_session(dev);
914 struct iscsi_transport *t = fnode_sess->transport;
915 int param;
916
917 if (attr == &dev_attr_fnode_auto_snd_tgt_disable.attr) {
918 param = ISCSI_FLASHNODE_AUTO_SND_TGT_DISABLE;
919 } else if (attr == &dev_attr_fnode_discovery_session.attr) {
920 param = ISCSI_FLASHNODE_DISCOVERY_SESS;
921 } else if (attr == &dev_attr_fnode_portal_type.attr) {
922 param = ISCSI_FLASHNODE_PORTAL_TYPE;
923 } else if (attr == &dev_attr_fnode_entry_enable.attr) {
924 param = ISCSI_FLASHNODE_ENTRY_EN;
925 } else if (attr == &dev_attr_fnode_immediate_data.attr) {
926 param = ISCSI_FLASHNODE_IMM_DATA_EN;
927 } else if (attr == &dev_attr_fnode_initial_r2t.attr) {
928 param = ISCSI_FLASHNODE_INITIAL_R2T_EN;
929 } else if (attr == &dev_attr_fnode_data_seq_in_order.attr) {
930 param = ISCSI_FLASHNODE_DATASEQ_INORDER;
931 } else if (attr == &dev_attr_fnode_data_pdu_in_order.attr) {

1220/**
1221 * iscsi_create_flashnode_sess - Add flashnode session entry in sysfs
1222 * @shost: pointer to host data
1223 * @index: index of flashnode to add in sysfs
1224 * @transport: pointer to transport data
1225 * @dd_size: total size to allocate
1226 *
1227 * Adds a sysfs entry for the flashnode session attributes
1228 *
1229 * Returns:
1230 * pointer to allocated flashnode sess on success
1231 * %NULL on failure
1232 */
1233struct iscsi_bus_flash_session *
1234iscsi_create_flashnode_sess(struct Scsi_Host *shost, int index,
1235 struct iscsi_transport *transport,
1236 int dd_size)
1237{
1238 struct iscsi_bus_flash_session *fnode_sess;
1239 int err;
1240
1241 fnode_sess = kzalloc(sizeof(*fnode_sess) + dd_size, GFP_KERNEL);
1242 if (!fnode_sess)
1243 return NULL;
1244
1245 fnode_sess->transport = transport;
1246 fnode_sess->target_id = index;
1247 fnode_sess->dev.type = &iscsi_flashnode_sess_dev_type;
1248 fnode_sess->dev.bus = &iscsi_flashnode_bus;
1249 fnode_sess->dev.parent = &shost->shost_gendev;
1250 dev_set_name(&fnode_sess->dev, "flashnode_sess-%u:%u",
1251 shost->host_no, index);
1252
1253 err = device_register(&fnode_sess->dev);
1254 if (err)
1255 goto free_fnode_sess;
1256
1257 if (dd_size)
1258 fnode_sess->dd_data = &fnode_sess[1];
1259
1260 return fnode_sess;
1261
1262free_fnode_sess:
1263 kfree(fnode_sess);
1264 return NULL;
1265}
1266EXPORT_SYMBOL_GPL(iscsi_create_flashnode_sess);
1267
1268/**
1269 * iscsi_create_flashnode_conn - Add flashnode conn entry in sysfs
1270 * @shost: pointer to host data
1271 * @fnode_sess: pointer to the parent flashnode session entry

1273 * @dd_size: total size to allocate

1338static int flashnode_match_index(struct device *dev, void *data)
1339{
1340 struct iscsi_bus_flash_session *fnode_sess = NULL;
1341 int ret = 0;
1342
1343 if (!iscsi_flashnode_bus_match(dev, NULL))
1344 goto exit_match_index;
1345
1346 fnode_sess = iscsi_dev_to_flash_session(dev);
1347 ret = (fnode_sess->target_id == *((int *)data)) ? 1 : 0;
1348
1349exit_match_index:
1350 return ret;
1351}

1353/**
1354 * iscsi_get_flashnode_by_index -finds flashnode session entry by index
1355 * @shost: pointer to host data
1356 * @idx: index to match
1357 *
1358 * Finds the flashnode session object for the passed index
1359 *
1360 * Returns:
1361 * pointer to found flashnode session object on success
1362 * %NULL on failure
1363 */
1364static struct iscsi_bus_flash_session *
1365iscsi_get_flashnode_by_index(struct Scsi_Host *shost, uint32_t idx)
1366{
1367 struct iscsi_bus_flash_session *fnode_sess = NULL;
1368 struct device *dev;
1369
1370 dev = device_find_child(&shost->shost_gendev, &idx,
1371 flashnode_match_index);
1372 if (dev)
1373 fnode_sess = iscsi_dev_to_flash_session(dev);
1374
1375 return fnode_sess;
1376}

1426/**
1427 * iscsi_destroy_flashnode_sess - destroy flashnode session entry
1428 * @fnode_sess: pointer to flashnode session entry to be destroyed
1429 *
1430 * Deletes the flashnode session entry and all children flashnode connection
1431 * entries from sysfs
1432 */
1433void iscsi_destroy_flashnode_sess(struct iscsi_bus_flash_session *fnode_sess)
1434{
1435 int err;
1436
1437 err = device_for_each_child(&fnode_sess->dev, NULL,
1438 iscsi_iter_destroy_flashnode_conn_fn);
1439 if (err)
1440 pr_err("Could not delete all connections for %s. Error %d.\n",
1441 fnode_sess->dev.kobj.name, err);
1442
1443 device_unregister(&fnode_sess->dev);
1444}
1445EXPORT_SYMBOL_GPL(iscsi_destroy_flashnode_sess);

1448{
1449 if (!iscsi_flashnode_bus_match(dev, NULL))
1450 return 0;
1451
1452 iscsi_destroy_flashnode_sess(iscsi_dev_to_flash_session(dev));
1453 return 0;
1454}

1470/*
1471 * BSG support
1472 */
1473/**
1474 * iscsi_bsg_host_dispatch - Dispatch command to LLD.
1475 * @job: bsg job to be processed
1476 */
1477static int iscsi_bsg_host_dispatch(struct bsg_job *job)
1478{
1479 struct Scsi_Host *shost = iscsi_job_to_shost(job);
1480 struct iscsi_bsg_request *req = job->request;
1481 struct iscsi_bsg_reply *reply = job->reply;
1482 struct iscsi_internal *i = to_iscsi_internal(shost->transportt);
1483 int cmdlen = sizeof(uint32_t); /* start with length of msgcode */
1484 int ret;
1485
1486 /* check if we have the msgcode value at least */
1487 if (job->request_len < sizeof(uint32_t)) {
1488 ret = -ENOMSG;
1489 goto fail_host_msg;
1490 }
1491
1492 /* Validate the host command */
1493 switch (req->msgcode) {
1494 case ISCSI_BSG_HST_VENDOR:
1495 cmdlen += sizeof(struct iscsi_bsg_host_vendor);
1496 if ((shost->hostt->vendor_id == 0L) ||
1497 (req->rqst_data.h_vendor.vendor_id !=
1498 shost->hostt->vendor_id)) {
1499 ret = -ESRCH;
1500 goto fail_host_msg;
1501 }
1502 break;
1503 default:
1504 ret = -EBADR;
1505 goto fail_host_msg;
1506 }
1507
1508 /* check if we really have all the request data needed */
1509 if (job->request_len < cmdlen) {
1510 ret = -ENOMSG;
1511 goto fail_host_msg;
1512 }
1513
1514 ret = i->iscsi_transport->bsg_request(job);
1515 if (!ret)
1516 return 0;
1517
1518fail_host_msg:
1519 /* return the errno failure code as the only status */
1520 BUG_ON(job->reply_len < sizeof(uint32_t));
1521 reply->reply_payload_rcv_len = 0;
1522 reply->result = ret;
1523 job->reply_len = sizeof(uint32_t);
1524 bsg_job_done(job, ret, 0);
1525 return 0;
1526}
1527
1528/**
1529 * iscsi_bsg_host_add - Create and add the bsg hooks to receive requests
1530 * @shost: shost for iscsi_host
1531 * @ihost: iscsi_cls_host adding the structures to
1532 */
1533static int
1534iscsi_bsg_host_add(struct Scsi_Host *shost, struct iscsi_cls_host *ihost)
1535{
1536 struct device *dev = &shost->shost_gendev;
1537 struct iscsi_internal *i = to_iscsi_internal(shost->transportt);
1538 struct request_queue *q;
1539 char bsg_name[20];
1540
1541 if (!i->iscsi_transport->bsg_request)
1542 return -ENOTSUPP;
1543
1544 snprintf(bsg_name, sizeof(bsg_name), "iscsi_host%d", shost->host_no);
1545 q = bsg_setup_queue(dev, bsg_name, iscsi_bsg_host_dispatch, 0, NULL);
1546 if (IS_ERR(q)) {
1547 shost_printk(KERN_ERR, shost, "bsg interface failed to "
1548 "initialize - no request queue\n");
1549 return PTR_ERR(q);
1550 }
1551 __scsi_init_queue(shost, q);
1552
1553 ihost->bsg_q = q;
1554 return 0;
1555}
1556
1557static int iscsi_setup_host(struct transport_container *tc, struct device *dev,
1558 struct device *cdev)
1559{
1560 struct Scsi_Host *shost = dev_to_shost(dev);
1561 struct iscsi_cls_host *ihost = shost->shost_data;
1562
1563 memset(ihost, 0, sizeof(*ihost));
1564 atomic_set(&ihost->nr_scans, 0);
1565 mutex_init(&ihost->mutex);
1566
1567 iscsi_bsg_host_add(shost, ihost);
1568 /* ignore any bsg add error - we just can't do sgio */
1569
1570 return 0;
1571}
1572
1573static int iscsi_remove_host(struct transport_container *tc,
1574 struct device *dev, struct device *cdev)
1575{
1576 struct Scsi_Host *shost = dev_to_shost(dev);
1577 struct iscsi_cls_host *ihost = shost->shost_data;
1578
1579 if (ihost->bsg_q) {
1580 bsg_unregister_queue(ihost->bsg_q);
1581 blk_cleanup_queue(ihost->bsg_q);
1582 }
1583 return 0;
1584}

1618/*
1619 * Returns the matching session to a given sid
1620 */
1621static struct iscsi_cls_session *iscsi_session_lookup(uint32_t sid)
1622{
1623 unsigned long flags;
1624 struct iscsi_cls_session *sess;
1625
1626 spin_lock_irqsave(&sesslock, flags);
1627 list_for_each_entry(sess, &sesslist, sess_list) {
1628 if (sess->sid == sid) {
1629 spin_unlock_irqrestore(&sesslock, flags);
1630 return sess;
1631 }
1632 }
1633 spin_unlock_irqrestore(&sesslock, flags);
1634 return NULL;
1635}
1636
1637/*
1638 * Returns the matching connection to a given sid / cid tuple
1639 */
1640static struct iscsi_cls_conn *iscsi_conn_lookup(uint32_t sid, uint32_t cid)
1641{
1642 unsigned long flags;
1643 struct iscsi_cls_conn *conn;
1644
1645 spin_lock_irqsave(&connlock, flags);
1646 list_for_each_entry(conn, &connlist, conn_list) {
1647 if ((conn->cid == cid) && (iscsi_conn_get_sid(conn) == sid)) {
1648 spin_unlock_irqrestore(&connlock, flags);
1649 return conn;
1650 }
1651 }
1652 spin_unlock_irqrestore(&connlock, flags);
1653 return NULL;
1654}

1656/*
1657 * The following functions can be used by LLDs that allocate
1658 * their own scsi_hosts or by software iscsi LLDs
1659 */
1660static struct {
1661 int value;
1662 char *name;
1663} iscsi_session_state_names[] = {
1664 { ISCSI_SESSION_LOGGED_IN, "LOGGED_IN" },
1665 { ISCSI_SESSION_FAILED, "FAILED" },
1666 { ISCSI_SESSION_FREE, "FREE" },
1667};
1668
1669static const char *iscsi_session_state_name(int state)
1670{
1671 int i;
1672 char *name = NULL;
1673
1674 for (i = 0; i < ARRAY_SIZE(iscsi_session_state_names); i++) {
1675 if (iscsi_session_state_names[i].value == state) {
1676 name = iscsi_session_state_names[i].name;
1677 break;
1678 }
1679 }
1680 return name;
1681}
1682
1683int iscsi_session_chkready(struct iscsi_cls_session *session)
1684{
1685 unsigned long flags;
1686 int err;
1687
1688 spin_lock_irqsave(&session->lock, flags);
1689 switch (session->state) {
1690 case ISCSI_SESSION_LOGGED_IN:
1691 err = 0;
1692 break;
1693 case ISCSI_SESSION_FAILED:
1694 err = DID_IMM_RETRY << 16;
1695 break;
1696 case ISCSI_SESSION_FREE:
1697 err = DID_TRANSPORT_FAILFAST << 16;
1698 break;
1699 default:
1700 err = DID_NO_CONNECT << 16;
1701 break;
1702 }
1703 spin_unlock_irqrestore(&session->lock, flags);
1704 return err;
1705}
1706EXPORT_SYMBOL_GPL(iscsi_session_chkready);

1708int iscsi_is_session_online(struct iscsi_cls_session *session)
1709{
1710 unsigned long flags;
1711 int ret = 0;
1712
1713 spin_lock_irqsave(&session->lock, flags);
1714 if (session->state == ISCSI_SESSION_LOGGED_IN)
1715 ret = 1;
1716 spin_unlock_irqrestore(&session->lock, flags);
1717 return ret;
1718}

1756/**
1757 * iscsi_scan_finished - helper to report when running scans are done
1758 * @shost: scsi host
1759 * @time: scan run time
1760 *
1761 * This function can be used by drives like qla4xxx to report to the scsi
1762 * layer when the scans it kicked off at module load time are done.
1763 */
1764int iscsi_scan_finished(struct Scsi_Host *shost, unsigned long time)
1765{
1766 struct iscsi_cls_host *ihost = shost->shost_data;
1767 /*
1768 * qla4xxx will have kicked off some session unblocks before calling
1769 * scsi_scan_host, so just wait for them to complete.
1770 */
1771 return !atomic_read(&ihost->nr_scans);
1772}
1773EXPORT_SYMBOL_GPL(iscsi_scan_finished);
1774
1775struct iscsi_scan_data {
1776 unsigned int channel;
1777 unsigned int id;
1778 u64 lun;
1779 enum scsi_scan_mode rescan;
1780};
1781
1782static int iscsi_user_scan_session(struct device *dev, void *data)
1783{
1784 struct iscsi_scan_data *scan_data = data;
1785 struct iscsi_cls_session *session;
1786 struct Scsi_Host *shost;
1787 struct iscsi_cls_host *ihost;
1788 unsigned long flags;
1789 unsigned int id;
1790
1791 if (!iscsi_is_session_dev(dev))
1792 return 0;
1793
1794 session = iscsi_dev_to_session(dev);
1795
1796 ISCSI_DBG_TRANS_SESSION(session, "Scanning session\n");
1797
1798 shost = iscsi_session_to_shost(session);
1799 ihost = shost->shost_data;
1800
1801 mutex_lock(&ihost->mutex);
1802 spin_lock_irqsave(&session->lock, flags);
1803 if (session->state != ISCSI_SESSION_LOGGED_IN) {
1804 spin_unlock_irqrestore(&session->lock, flags);
1805 goto user_scan_exit;
1806 }
1807 id = session->target_id;
1808 spin_unlock_irqrestore(&session->lock, flags);
1809
1810 if (id != ISCSI_MAX_TARGET) {
1811 if ((scan_data->channel == SCAN_WILD_CARD ||
1812 scan_data->channel == 0) &&
1813 (scan_data->id == SCAN_WILD_CARD ||
1814 scan_data->id == id))
1815 scsi_scan_target(&session->dev, 0, id,
1816 scan_data->lun, scan_data->rescan);
1817 }
1818
1819user_scan_exit:
1820 mutex_unlock(&ihost->mutex);
1821 ISCSI_DBG_TRANS_SESSION(session, "Completed session scan\n");
1822 return 0;
1823}
1824
1825static int iscsi_user_scan(struct Scsi_Host *shost, uint channel,
1826 uint id, u64 lun)
1827{
1828 struct iscsi_scan_data scan_data;
1829
1830 scan_data.channel = channel;
1831 scan_data.id = id;
1832 scan_data.lun = lun;
1833 scan_data.rescan = SCSI_SCAN_MANUAL;
1834
1835 return device_for_each_child(&shost->shost_gendev, &scan_data,
1836 iscsi_user_scan_session);
1837}
1838
1839static void iscsi_scan_session(struct work_struct *work)
1840{
1841 struct iscsi_cls_session *session =
1842 container_of(work, struct iscsi_cls_session, scan_work);
1843 struct Scsi_Host *shost = iscsi_session_to_shost(session);
1844 struct iscsi_cls_host *ihost = shost->shost_data;
1845 struct iscsi_scan_data scan_data;
1846
1847 scan_data.channel = 0;
1848 scan_data.id = SCAN_WILD_CARD;
1849 scan_data.lun = SCAN_WILD_CARD;
1850 scan_data.rescan = SCSI_SCAN_RESCAN;
1851
1852 iscsi_user_scan_session(&session->dev, &scan_data);
1853 atomic_dec(&ihost->nr_scans);
1854}
1855
1856/**
1857 * iscsi_block_scsi_eh - block scsi eh until session state has transistioned
1858 * @cmd: scsi cmd passed to scsi eh handler
1859 *
1860 * If the session is down this function will wait for the recovery
1861 * timer to fire or for the session to be logged back in. If the
1862 * recovery timer fires then FAST_IO_FAIL is returned. The caller
1863 * should pass this error value to the scsi eh.
1864 */
1865int iscsi_block_scsi_eh(struct scsi_cmnd *cmd)
1866{
1867 struct iscsi_cls_session *session =
1868 starget_to_session(scsi_target(cmd->device));
1869 unsigned long flags;
1870 int ret = 0;
1871
1872 spin_lock_irqsave(&session->lock, flags);
1873 while (session->state != ISCSI_SESSION_LOGGED_IN) {
1874 if (session->state == ISCSI_SESSION_FREE) {
1875 ret = FAST_IO_FAIL;
1876 break;
1877 }
1878 spin_unlock_irqrestore(&session->lock, flags);
1879 msleep(1000);
1880 spin_lock_irqsave(&session->lock, flags);
1881 }
1882 spin_unlock_irqrestore(&session->lock, flags);
1883 return ret;
1884}
1885EXPORT_SYMBOL_GPL(iscsi_block_scsi_eh);
1886
1887static void session_recovery_timedout(struct work_struct *work)
1888{
1889 struct iscsi_cls_session *session =
1890 container_of(work, struct iscsi_cls_session,
1891 recovery_work.work);
1892 unsigned long flags;
1893
1894 iscsi_cls_session_printk(KERN_INFO, session,
1895 "session recovery timed out after %d secs\n",
1896 session->recovery_tmo);
1897
1898 spin_lock_irqsave(&session->lock, flags);
1899 switch (session->state) {
1900 case ISCSI_SESSION_FAILED:
1901 session->state = ISCSI_SESSION_FREE;
1902 break;
1903 case ISCSI_SESSION_LOGGED_IN:
1904 case ISCSI_SESSION_FREE:
1905 /* we raced with the unblock's flush */
1906 spin_unlock_irqrestore(&session->lock, flags);
1907 return;
1908 }
1909 spin_unlock_irqrestore(&session->lock, flags);
1910
1911 if (session->transport->session_recovery_timedout)
1912 session->transport->session_recovery_timedout(session);
1913
1914 ISCSI_DBG_TRANS_SESSION(session, "Unblocking SCSI target\n");
1915 scsi_target_unblock(&session->dev, SDEV_TRANSPORT_OFFLINE);
1916 ISCSI_DBG_TRANS_SESSION(session, "Completed unblocking SCSI target\n");
1917}
1918
1919static void __iscsi_unblock_session(struct work_struct *work)
1920{
1921 struct iscsi_cls_session *session =
1922 container_of(work, struct iscsi_cls_session,
1923 unblock_work);
1924 struct Scsi_Host *shost = iscsi_session_to_shost(session);
1925 struct iscsi_cls_host *ihost = shost->shost_data;
1926 unsigned long flags;
1927
1928 ISCSI_DBG_TRANS_SESSION(session, "Unblocking session\n");
1929 /*
1930 * The recovery and unblock work get run from the same workqueue,
1931 * so try to cancel it if it was going to run after this unblock.
1932 */
1933 cancel_delayed_work(&session->recovery_work);
1934 spin_lock_irqsave(&session->lock, flags);
1935 session->state = ISCSI_SESSION_LOGGED_IN;
1936 spin_unlock_irqrestore(&session->lock, flags);
1937 /* start IO */
1938 scsi_target_unblock(&session->dev, SDEV_RUNNING);
1939 /*
1940 * Only do kernel scanning if the driver is properly hooked into
1941 * the async scanning code (drivers like iscsi_tcp do login and
1942 * scanning from userspace).
1943 */
1944 if (shost->hostt->scan_finished) {
1945 if (scsi_queue_work(shost, &session->scan_work))
1946 atomic_inc(&ihost->nr_scans);
1947 }
1948 ISCSI_DBG_TRANS_SESSION(session, "Completed unblocking session\n");
1949}
1950
1951/**
1952 * iscsi_unblock_session - set a session as logged in and start IO.
1953 * @session: iscsi session
1954 *
1955 * Mark a session as ready to accept IO.
1956 */
1957void iscsi_unblock_session(struct iscsi_cls_session *session)
1958{
1959 queue_work(iscsi_eh_timer_workq, &session->unblock_work);
1960 /*
1961 * make sure all the events have completed before tell the driver
1962 * it is safe
1963 */
1964 flush_workqueue(iscsi_eh_timer_workq);
1965}
1966EXPORT_SYMBOL_GPL(iscsi_unblock_session);
1967
1968static void __iscsi_block_session(struct work_struct *work)
1969{
1970 struct iscsi_cls_session *session =
1971 container_of(work, struct iscsi_cls_session,
1972 block_work);
1973 unsigned long flags;
1974
1975 ISCSI_DBG_TRANS_SESSION(session, "Blocking session\n");
1976 spin_lock_irqsave(&session->lock, flags);
1977 session->state = ISCSI_SESSION_FAILED;
1978 spin_unlock_irqrestore(&session->lock, flags);
1979 scsi_target_block(&session->dev);
1980 ISCSI_DBG_TRANS_SESSION(session, "Completed SCSI target blocking\n");
1981 if (session->recovery_tmo >= 0)
1982 queue_delayed_work(iscsi_eh_timer_workq,
1983 &session->recovery_work,
1984 session->recovery_tmo * HZ);
1985}
1986
1987void iscsi_block_session(struct iscsi_cls_session *session)
1988{
1989 queue_work(iscsi_eh_timer_workq, &session->block_work);
1990}
1991EXPORT_SYMBOL_GPL(iscsi_block_session);
1992
1993static void __iscsi_unbind_session(struct work_struct *work)
1994{
1995 struct iscsi_cls_session *session =
1996 container_of(work, struct iscsi_cls_session,
1997 unbind_work);
1998 struct Scsi_Host *shost = iscsi_session_to_shost(session);
1999 struct iscsi_cls_host *ihost = shost->shost_data;
2000 unsigned long flags;
2001 unsigned int target_id;
2002
2003 ISCSI_DBG_TRANS_SESSION(session, "Unbinding session\n");
2004
2005 /* Prevent new scans and make sure scanning is not in progress */
2006 mutex_lock(&ihost->mutex);
2007 spin_lock_irqsave(&session->lock, flags);
2008 if (session->target_id == ISCSI_MAX_TARGET) {
2009 spin_unlock_irqrestore(&session->lock, flags);
2010 mutex_unlock(&ihost->mutex);
2011 return;
2012 }
2013
2014 target_id = session->target_id;
2015 session->target_id = ISCSI_MAX_TARGET;
2016 spin_unlock_irqrestore(&session->lock, flags);
2017 mutex_unlock(&ihost->mutex);
2018
2019 if (session->ida_used)
2020 ida_simple_remove(&iscsi_sess_ida, target_id);
2021
2022 scsi_remove_target(&session->dev);
2023 iscsi_session_event(session, ISCSI_KEVENT_UNBIND_SESSION);
2024 ISCSI_DBG_TRANS_SESSION(session, "Completed target removal\n");
2025}
2026
2027struct iscsi_cls_session *
2028iscsi_alloc_session(struct Scsi_Host *shost, struct iscsi_transport *transport,
2029 int dd_size)
2030{
2031 struct iscsi_cls_session *session;
2032
2033 session = kzalloc(sizeof(*session) + dd_size,
2034 GFP_KERNEL);
2035 if (!session)
2036 return NULL;
2037
2038 session->transport = transport;
2039 session->creator = -1;
2040 session->recovery_tmo = 120;
2041 session->recovery_tmo_sysfs_override = false;
2042 session->state = ISCSI_SESSION_FREE;
2043 INIT_DELAYED_WORK(&session->recovery_work, session_recovery_timedout);
2044 INIT_LIST_HEAD(&session->sess_list);
2045 INIT_WORK(&session->unblock_work, __iscsi_unblock_session);
2046 INIT_WORK(&session->block_work, __iscsi_block_session);
2047 INIT_WORK(&session->unbind_work, __iscsi_unbind_session);
2048 INIT_WORK(&session->scan_work, iscsi_scan_session);
2049 spin_lock_init(&session->lock);
2050
2051 /* this is released in the dev's release function */
2052 scsi_host_get(shost);
2053 session->dev.parent = &shost->shost_gendev;
2054 session->dev.release = iscsi_session_release;
2055 device_initialize(&session->dev);
2056 if (dd_size)
2057 session->dd_data = &session[1];
2058
2059 ISCSI_DBG_TRANS_SESSION(session, "Completed session allocation\n");
2060 return session;
2061}
2062EXPORT_SYMBOL_GPL(iscsi_alloc_session);
2063
2064int iscsi_add_session(struct iscsi_cls_session *session, unsigned int target_id)
2065{
2066 unsigned long flags;
2067 int id = 0;
2068 int err;
2069
2070 session->sid = atomic_add_return(1, &iscsi_session_nr);
2071
2072 if (target_id == ISCSI_MAX_TARGET) {
2073 id = ida_simple_get(&iscsi_sess_ida, 0, 0, GFP_KERNEL);
2074
2075 if (id < 0) {
2076 iscsi_cls_session_printk(KERN_ERR, session,
2077 "Failure in Target ID Allocation\n");
2078 return id;
2079 }
2080 session->target_id = (unsigned int)id;
2081 session->ida_used = true;
2082 } else
2083 session->target_id = target_id;
2084
2085 dev_set_name(&session->dev, "session%u", session->sid);
2086 err = device_add(&session->dev);
2087 if (err) {
2088 iscsi_cls_session_printk(KERN_ERR, session,
2089 "could not register session's dev\n");
2090 goto release_ida;
2091 }
2092 transport_register_device(&session->dev);
2093
2094 spin_lock_irqsave(&sesslock, flags);
2095 list_add(&session->sess_list, &sesslist);
2096 spin_unlock_irqrestore(&sesslock, flags);
2097
2098 iscsi_session_event(session, ISCSI_KEVENT_CREATE_SESSION);
2099 ISCSI_DBG_TRANS_SESSION(session, "Completed session adding\n");
2100 return 0;
2101
2102release_ida:
2103 if (session->ida_used)
2104 ida_simple_remove(&iscsi_sess_ida, session->target_id);
2105
2106 return err;
2107}
2108EXPORT_SYMBOL_GPL(iscsi_add_session);

2140 struct device *parent = conn->dev.parent;

2159void iscsi_remove_session(struct iscsi_cls_session *session)
2160{
2161 unsigned long flags;
2162 int err;
2163
2164 ISCSI_DBG_TRANS_SESSION(session, "Removing session\n");
2165
2166 spin_lock_irqsave(&sesslock, flags);
2167 list_del(&session->sess_list);
2168 spin_unlock_irqrestore(&sesslock, flags);
2169
2170 /* make sure there are no blocks/unblocks queued */
2171 flush_workqueue(iscsi_eh_timer_workq);
2172 /* make sure the timedout callout is not running */
2173 if (!cancel_delayed_work(&session->recovery_work))
2174 flush_workqueue(iscsi_eh_timer_workq);
2175 /*
2176 * If we are blocked let commands flow again. The lld or iscsi
2177 * layer should set up the queuecommand to fail commands.
2178 * We assume that LLD will not be calling block/unblock while
2179 * removing the session.
2180 */
2181 spin_lock_irqsave(&session->lock, flags);
2182 session->state = ISCSI_SESSION_FREE;
2183 spin_unlock_irqrestore(&session->lock, flags);
2184
2185 scsi_target_unblock(&session->dev, SDEV_TRANSPORT_OFFLINE);
2186 /* flush running scans then delete devices */
2187 flush_work(&session->scan_work);
2188 __iscsi_unbind_session(&session->unbind_work);
2189
2190 /* hw iscsi may not have removed all connections from session */
2191 err = device_for_each_child(&session->dev, NULL,
2192 iscsi_iter_destroy_conn_fn);
2193 if (err)
2194 iscsi_cls_session_printk(KERN_ERR, session,
2195 "Could not delete all connections "
2196 "for session. Error %d.\n", err);
2197
2198 transport_unregister_device(&session->dev);
2199
2200 ISCSI_DBG_TRANS_SESSION(session, "Completing session removal\n");
2201 device_del(&session->dev);
2202}
2203EXPORT_SYMBOL_GPL(iscsi_remove_session);

2207 ISCSI_DBG_TRANS_SESSION(session, "Freeing session\n");
2208 iscsi_session_event(session, ISCSI_KEVENT_DESTROY_SESSION);
2209 put_device(&session->dev);
2210}

2213/**
2214 * iscsi_create_conn - create iscsi class connection
2215 * @session: iscsi cls session
2216 * @dd_size: private driver data size
2217 * @cid: connection id
2218 *
2219 * This can be called from a LLD or iscsi_transport. The connection
2220 * is child of the session so cid must be unique for all connections
2221 * on the session.
2222 *
2223 * Since we do not support MCS, cid will normally be zero. In some cases
2224 * for software iscsi we could be trying to preallocate a connection struct
2225 * in which case there could be two connection structs and cid would be
2226 * non-zero.
2227 */
2228struct iscsi_cls_conn *
2229iscsi_create_conn(struct iscsi_cls_session *session, int dd_size, uint32_t cid)
2230{
2231 struct iscsi_transport *transport = session->transport;
2232 struct iscsi_cls_conn *conn;
2233 unsigned long flags;
2234 int err;
2235
2236 conn = kzalloc(sizeof(*conn) + dd_size, GFP_KERNEL);
2237 if (!conn)
2238 return NULL;
2239 if (dd_size)
2240 conn->dd_data = &conn[1];
2241
2242 mutex_init(&conn->ep_mutex);
2243 INIT_LIST_HEAD(&conn->conn_list);
2244 conn->transport = transport;
2245 conn->cid = cid;
2246
2247 /* this is released in the dev's release function */
2248 if (!get_device(&session->dev))
2249 goto free_conn;
2250
2251 dev_set_name(&conn->dev, "connection%d:%u", session->sid, cid);
2252 conn->dev.parent = &session->dev;
2253 conn->dev.release = iscsi_conn_release;
2254 err = device_register(&conn->dev);
2255 if (err) {
2256 iscsi_cls_session_printk(KERN_ERR, session, "could not "
2257 "register connection's dev\n");
2258 goto release_parent_ref;
2259 }
2260 transport_register_device(&conn->dev);
2261
2262 spin_lock_irqsave(&connlock, flags);
2263 list_add(&conn->conn_list, &connlist);
2264 spin_unlock_irqrestore(&connlock, flags);
2265
2266 ISCSI_DBG_TRANS_CONN(conn, "Completed conn creation\n");
2267 return conn;
2268
2269release_parent_ref:
2270 put_device(&session->dev);
2271free_conn:
2272 kfree(conn);
2273 return NULL;
2274}
2275
2276EXPORT_SYMBOL_GPL(iscsi_create_conn);

2282 * This can be called from a LLD or iscsi_transport.
2283 */
2284int iscsi_destroy_conn(struct iscsi_cls_conn *conn)

2287

2331int iscsi_recv_pdu(struct iscsi_cls_conn *conn, struct iscsi_hdr *hdr,
2332 char *data, uint32_t data_size)
2333{
2334 struct nlmsghdr *nlh;
2335 struct sk_buff *skb;
2336 struct iscsi_uevent *ev;
2337 char *pdu;
2338 struct iscsi_internal *priv;
2339 int len = nlmsg_total_size(sizeof(*ev) + sizeof(struct iscsi_hdr) +
2340 data_size);
2341
2342 priv = iscsi_if_transport_lookup(conn->transport);
2343 if (!priv)
2344 return -EINVAL;
2345
2346 skb = alloc_skb(len, GFP_ATOMIC);
2347 if (!skb) {
2348 iscsi_conn_error_event(conn, ISCSI_ERR_CONN_FAILED);
2349 iscsi_cls_conn_printk(KERN_ERR, conn, "can not deliver "
2350 "control PDU: OOM\n");
2351 return -ENOMEM;
2352 }
2353
2354 nlh = __nlmsg_put(skb, 0, 0, 0, (len - sizeof(*nlh)), 0);
2355 ev = nlmsg_data(nlh);
2356 memset(ev, 0, sizeof(*ev));
2357 ev->transport_handle = iscsi_handle(conn->transport);
2358 ev->type = ISCSI_KEVENT_RECV_PDU;
2359 ev->r.recv_req.cid = conn->cid;
2360 ev->r.recv_req.sid = iscsi_conn_get_sid(conn);
2361 pdu = (char*)ev + sizeof(*ev);
2362 memcpy(pdu, hdr, sizeof(struct iscsi_hdr));
2363 memcpy(pdu + sizeof(struct iscsi_hdr), data, data_size);
2364
2365 return iscsi_multicast_skb(skb, ISCSI_NL_GRP_ISCSID, GFP_ATOMIC);
2366}
2367EXPORT_SYMBOL_GPL(iscsi_recv_pdu);

2550static int
2551iscsi_if_get_stats(struct iscsi_transport *transport, struct nlmsghdr *nlh)
2552{
2553 struct iscsi_uevent *ev = nlmsg_data(nlh);
2554 struct iscsi_stats *stats;
2555 struct sk_buff *skbstat;
2556 struct iscsi_cls_conn *conn;
2557 struct nlmsghdr *nlhstat;
2558 struct iscsi_uevent *evstat;
2559 struct iscsi_internal *priv;
2560 int len = nlmsg_total_size(sizeof(*ev) +
2561 sizeof(struct iscsi_stats) +
2562 sizeof(struct iscsi_stats_custom) *
2563 ISCSI_STATS_CUSTOM_MAX);
2564 int err = 0;
2565
2566 priv = iscsi_if_transport_lookup(transport);
2567 if (!priv)
2568 return -EINVAL;
2569
2570 conn = iscsi_conn_lookup(ev->u.get_stats.sid, ev->u.get_stats.cid);
2571 if (!conn)
2572 return -EEXIST;
2573
2574 do {
2575 int actual_size;
2576
2577 skbstat = alloc_skb(len, GFP_ATOMIC);
2578 if (!skbstat) {
2579 iscsi_cls_conn_printk(KERN_ERR, conn, "can not "
2580 "deliver stats: OOM\n");
2581 return -ENOMEM;
2582 }
2583
2584 nlhstat = __nlmsg_put(skbstat, 0, 0, 0,
2585 (len - sizeof(*nlhstat)), 0);
2586 evstat = nlmsg_data(nlhstat);
2587 memset(evstat, 0, sizeof(*evstat));
2588 evstat->transport_handle = iscsi_handle(conn->transport);
2589 evstat->type = nlh->nlmsg_type;
2590 evstat->u.get_stats.cid =
2591 ev->u.get_stats.cid;
2592 evstat->u.get_stats.sid =
2593 ev->u.get_stats.sid;
2594 stats = (struct iscsi_stats *)
2595 ((char*)evstat + sizeof(*evstat));
2596 memset(stats, 0, sizeof(*stats));
2597
2598 transport->get_stats(conn, stats);
2599 actual_size = nlmsg_total_size(sizeof(struct iscsi_uevent) +
2600 sizeof(struct iscsi_stats) +
2601 sizeof(struct iscsi_stats_custom) *
2602 stats->custom_length);
2603 actual_size -= sizeof(*nlhstat);
2604 actual_size = nlmsg_msg_size(actual_size);
2605 skb_trim(skbstat, NLMSG_ALIGN(actual_size));
2606 nlhstat->nlmsg_len = actual_size;
2607
2608 err = iscsi_multicast_skb(skbstat, ISCSI_NL_GRP_ISCSID,
2609 GFP_ATOMIC);
2610 } while (err < 0 && err != -ECONNREFUSED);
2611
2612 return err;
2613}

2615/**
2616 * iscsi_session_event - send session destr. completion event
2617 * @session: iscsi class session
2618 * @event: type of event
2619 */
2620int iscsi_session_event(struct iscsi_cls_session *session,
2621 enum iscsi_uevent_e event)
2622{
2623 struct iscsi_internal *priv;
2624 struct Scsi_Host *shost;
2625 struct iscsi_uevent *ev;
2626 struct sk_buff *skb;
2627 struct nlmsghdr *nlh;
2628 int rc, len = nlmsg_total_size(sizeof(*ev));
2629
2630 priv = iscsi_if_transport_lookup(session->transport);
2631 if (!priv)
2632 return -EINVAL;
2633 shost = iscsi_session_to_shost(session);
2634
2635 skb = alloc_skb(len, GFP_KERNEL);
2636 if (!skb) {
2637 iscsi_cls_session_printk(KERN_ERR, session,
2638 "Cannot notify userspace of session "
2639 "event %u\n", event);
2640 return -ENOMEM;
2641 }
2642
2643 nlh = __nlmsg_put(skb, 0, 0, 0, (len - sizeof(*nlh)), 0);
2644 ev = nlmsg_data(nlh);
2645 ev->transport_handle = iscsi_handle(session->transport);
2646
2647 ev->type = event;
2648 switch (event) {
2649 case ISCSI_KEVENT_DESTROY_SESSION:
2650 ev->r.d_session.host_no = shost->host_no;
2651 ev->r.d_session.sid = session->sid;
2652 break;
2653 case ISCSI_KEVENT_CREATE_SESSION:
2654 ev->r.c_session_ret.host_no = shost->host_no;
2655 ev->r.c_session_ret.sid = session->sid;
2656 break;
2657 case ISCSI_KEVENT_UNBIND_SESSION:
2658 ev->r.unbind_session.host_no = shost->host_no;
2659 ev->r.unbind_session.sid = session->sid;
2660 break;
2661 default:
2662 iscsi_cls_session_printk(KERN_ERR, session, "Invalid event "
2663 "%u.\n", event);
2664 kfree_skb(skb);
2665 return -EINVAL;
2666 }
2667
2668 /*
2669 * this will occur if the daemon is not up, so we just warn
2670 * the user and when the daemon is restarted it will handle it
2671 */
2672 rc = iscsi_multicast_skb(skb, ISCSI_NL_GRP_ISCSID, GFP_KERNEL);
2673 if (rc == -ESRCH)
2674 iscsi_cls_session_printk(KERN_ERR, session,
2675 "Cannot notify userspace of session "
2676 "event %u. Check iscsi daemon\n",
2677 event);
2678
2679 ISCSI_DBG_TRANS_SESSION(session, "Completed handling event %d rc %d\n",
2680 event, rc);
2681 return rc;
2682}
2683EXPORT_SYMBOL_GPL(iscsi_session_event);
2684
2685static int
2686iscsi_if_create_session(struct iscsi_internal *priv, struct iscsi_endpoint *ep,
2687 struct iscsi_uevent *ev, pid_t pid,
2688 uint32_t initial_cmdsn, uint16_t cmds_max,
2689 uint16_t queue_depth)
2690{
2691 struct iscsi_transport *transport = priv->iscsi_transport;
2692 struct iscsi_cls_session *session;
2693 struct Scsi_Host *shost;
2694
2695 session = transport->create_session(ep, cmds_max, queue_depth,
2696 initial_cmdsn);
2697 if (!session)
2698 return -ENOMEM;
2699
2700 session->creator = pid;
2701 shost = iscsi_session_to_shost(session);
2702 ev->r.c_session_ret.host_no = shost->host_no;
2703 ev->r.c_session_ret.sid = session->sid;
2704 ISCSI_DBG_TRANS_SESSION(session,
2705 "Completed creating transport session\n");
2706 return 0;
2707}

2710iscsi_if_create_conn(struct iscsi_transport *transport, struct iscsi_uevent *ev)
2711{

2714
2715 session = iscsi_session_lookup(ev->u.c_conn.sid);

2730 ev->r.c_conn_ret.cid = conn->cid;

2733 return 0;

2752static int
2753iscsi_set_param(struct iscsi_transport *transport, struct iscsi_uevent *ev)
2754{
2755 char *data = (char*)ev + sizeof(*ev);
2756 struct iscsi_cls_conn *conn;
2757 struct iscsi_cls_session *session;
2758 int err = 0, value = 0;
2759
2760 session = iscsi_session_lookup(ev->u.set_param.sid);
2761 conn = iscsi_conn_lookup(ev->u.set_param.sid, ev->u.set_param.cid);
2762 if (!conn || !session)
2763 return -EINVAL;
2764
2765 switch (ev->u.set_param.param) {
2766 case ISCSI_PARAM_SESS_RECOVERY_TMO:
2767 sscanf(data, "%d", &value);
2768 if (!session->recovery_tmo_sysfs_override)
2769 session->recovery_tmo = value;
2770 break;
2771 default:
2772 err = transport->set_param(conn, ev->u.set_param.param,
2773 data, ev->u.set_param.len);
2774 }
2775
2776 return err;
2777}

2779static int iscsi_if_ep_connect(struct iscsi_transport *transport,
2780 struct iscsi_uevent *ev, int msg_type)
2781{
2782 struct iscsi_endpoint *ep;
2783 struct sockaddr *dst_addr;
2784 struct Scsi_Host *shost = NULL;
2785 int non_blocking, err = 0;
2786
2787 if (!transport->ep_connect)
2788 return -EINVAL;
2789
2790 if (msg_type == ISCSI_UEVENT_TRANSPORT_EP_CONNECT_THROUGH_HOST) {
2791 shost = scsi_host_lookup(ev->u.ep_connect_through_host.host_no);
2792 if (!shost) {
2793 printk(KERN_ERR "ep connect failed. Could not find "
2794 "host no %u\n",
2795 ev->u.ep_connect_through_host.host_no);
2796 return -ENODEV;
2797 }
2798 non_blocking = ev->u.ep_connect_through_host.non_blocking;
2799 } else
2800 non_blocking = ev->u.ep_connect.non_blocking;
2801
2802 dst_addr = (struct sockaddr *)((char*)ev + sizeof(*ev));
2803 ep = transport->ep_connect(shost, dst_addr, non_blocking);
2804 if (IS_ERR(ep)) {
2805 err = PTR_ERR(ep);
2806 goto release_host;
2807 }
2808
2809 ev->r.ep_connect_ret.handle = ep->id;
2810release_host:
2811 if (shost)
2812 scsi_host_put(shost);
2813 return err;
2814}
2815
2816static int iscsi_if_ep_disconnect(struct iscsi_transport *transport,
2817 u64 ep_handle)
2818{
2819 struct iscsi_cls_conn *conn;
2820 struct iscsi_endpoint *ep;
2821
2822 if (!transport->ep_disconnect)
2823 return -EINVAL;
2824
2825 ep = iscsi_lookup_endpoint(ep_handle);
2826 if (!ep)
2827 return -EINVAL;
2828 conn = ep->conn;
2829 if (conn) {
2830 mutex_lock(&conn->ep_mutex);
2831 conn->ep = NULL;
2832 mutex_unlock(&conn->ep_mutex);
2833 }
2834
2835 transport->ep_disconnect(ep);
2836 return 0;
2837}
2838
2839static int
2840iscsi_if_transport_ep(struct iscsi_transport *transport,
2841 struct iscsi_uevent *ev, int msg_type)
2842{
2843 struct iscsi_endpoint *ep;
2844 int rc = 0;
2845
2846 switch (msg_type) {
2847 case ISCSI_UEVENT_TRANSPORT_EP_CONNECT_THROUGH_HOST:
2848 case ISCSI_UEVENT_TRANSPORT_EP_CONNECT:
2849 rc = iscsi_if_ep_connect(transport, ev, msg_type);
2850 break;
2851 case ISCSI_UEVENT_TRANSPORT_EP_POLL:
2852 if (!transport->ep_poll)
2853 return -EINVAL;
2854
2855 ep = iscsi_lookup_endpoint(ev->u.ep_poll.ep_handle);
2856 if (!ep)
2857 return -EINVAL;
2858
2859 ev->r.retcode = transport->ep_poll(ep,
2860 ev->u.ep_poll.timeout_ms);
2861 break;
2862 case ISCSI_UEVENT_TRANSPORT_EP_DISCONNECT:
2863 rc = iscsi_if_ep_disconnect(transport,
2864 ev->u.ep_disconnect.ep_handle);
2865 break;
2866 }
2867 return rc;
2868}

2994static int
2995iscsi_get_chap(struct iscsi_transport *transport, struct nlmsghdr *nlh)
2996{
2997 struct iscsi_uevent *ev = nlmsg_data(nlh);
2998 struct Scsi_Host *shost = NULL;
2999 struct iscsi_chap_rec *chap_rec;
3000 struct iscsi_internal *priv;
3001 struct sk_buff *skbchap;
3002 struct nlmsghdr *nlhchap;
3003 struct iscsi_uevent *evchap;
3004 uint32_t chap_buf_size;
3005 int len, err = 0;
3006 char *buf;
3007
3008 if (!transport->get_chap)
3009 return -EINVAL;
3010
3011 priv = iscsi_if_transport_lookup(transport);
3012 if (!priv)
3013 return -EINVAL;
3014
3015 chap_buf_size = (ev->u.get_chap.num_entries * sizeof(*chap_rec));
3016 len = nlmsg_total_size(sizeof(*ev) + chap_buf_size);
3017
3018 shost = scsi_host_lookup(ev->u.get_chap.host_no);
3019 if (!shost) {
3020 printk(KERN_ERR "%s: failed. Could not find host no %u\n",
3021 __func__, ev->u.get_chap.host_no);
3022 return -ENODEV;
3023 }
3024
3025 do {
3026 int actual_size;
3027
3028 skbchap = alloc_skb(len, GFP_KERNEL);
3029 if (!skbchap) {
3030 printk(KERN_ERR "can not deliver chap: OOM\n");
3031 err = -ENOMEM;
3032 goto exit_get_chap;
3033 }
3034
3035 nlhchap = __nlmsg_put(skbchap, 0, 0, 0,
3036 (len - sizeof(*nlhchap)), 0);
3037 evchap = nlmsg_data(nlhchap);
3038 memset(evchap, 0, sizeof(*evchap));
3039 evchap->transport_handle = iscsi_handle(transport);
3040 evchap->type = nlh->nlmsg_type;
3041 evchap->u.get_chap.host_no = ev->u.get_chap.host_no;
3042 evchap->u.get_chap.chap_tbl_idx = ev->u.get_chap.chap_tbl_idx;
3043 evchap->u.get_chap.num_entries = ev->u.get_chap.num_entries;
3044 buf = (char *)evchap + sizeof(*evchap);
3045 memset(buf, 0, chap_buf_size);
3046
3047 err = transport->get_chap(shost, ev->u.get_chap.chap_tbl_idx,
3048 &evchap->u.get_chap.num_entries, buf);
3049
3050 actual_size = nlmsg_total_size(sizeof(*ev) + chap_buf_size);
3051 skb_trim(skbchap, NLMSG_ALIGN(actual_size));
3052 nlhchap->nlmsg_len = actual_size;
3053
3054 err = iscsi_multicast_skb(skbchap, ISCSI_NL_GRP_ISCSID,
3055 GFP_KERNEL);
3056 } while (err < 0 && err != -ECONNREFUSED);
3057
3058exit_get_chap:
3059 scsi_host_put(shost);
3060 return err;
3061}

3365{
3366 struct Scsi_Host *shost;
3367 struct iscsi_cls_session *session;
3368 int err = 0;
3369
3370 if (!transport->logout_flashnode_sid) {
3371 err = -ENOSYS;
3372 goto exit_logout_sid;
3373 }
3374
3375 shost = scsi_host_lookup(ev->u.logout_flashnode_sid.host_no);
3376 if (!shost) {
3377 pr_err("%s could not find host no %u\n",
3378 __func__, ev->u.logout_flashnode.host_no);
3379 err = -ENODEV;
3380 goto put_host;
3381 }
3382
3383 session = iscsi_session_lookup(ev->u.logout_flashnode_sid.sid);
3384 if (!session) {
3385 pr_err("%s could not find session id %u\n",
3386 __func__, ev->u.logout_flashnode_sid.sid);
3387 err = -EINVAL;
3388 goto put_host;
3389 }
3390
3391 err = transport->logout_flashnode_sid(session);
3392
3393put_host:
3394 scsi_host_put(shost);
3395
3396exit_logout_sid:
3397 return err;
3398}
3399
3400static int
3401iscsi_get_host_stats(struct iscsi_transport *transport, struct nlmsghdr *nlh)
3402{
3403 struct iscsi_uevent *ev = nlmsg_data(nlh);
3404 struct Scsi_Host *shost = NULL;
3405 struct iscsi_internal *priv;
3406 struct sk_buff *skbhost_stats;
3407 struct nlmsghdr *nlhhost_stats;
3408 struct iscsi_uevent *evhost_stats;
3409 int host_stats_size = 0;
3410 int len, err = 0;
3411 char *buf;
3412
3413 if (!transport->get_host_stats)
3414 return -ENOSYS;
3415
3416 priv = iscsi_if_transport_lookup(transport);
3417 if (!priv)
3418 return -EINVAL;
3419
3420 host_stats_size = sizeof(struct iscsi_offload_host_stats);
3421 len = nlmsg_total_size(sizeof(*ev) + host_stats_size);
3422
3423 shost = scsi_host_lookup(ev->u.get_host_stats.host_no);
3424 if (!shost) {
3425 pr_err("%s: failed. Cound not find host no %u\n",
3426 __func__, ev->u.get_host_stats.host_no);
3427 return -ENODEV;
3428 }
3429
3430 do {
3431 int actual_size;
3432
3433 skbhost_stats = alloc_skb(len, GFP_KERNEL);
3434 if (!skbhost_stats) {
3435 pr_err("cannot deliver host stats: OOM\n");
3436 err = -ENOMEM;
3437 goto exit_host_stats;
3438 }
3439
3440 nlhhost_stats = __nlmsg_put(skbhost_stats, 0, 0, 0,
3441 (len - sizeof(*nlhhost_stats)), 0);
3442 evhost_stats = nlmsg_data(nlhhost_stats);
3443 memset(evhost_stats, 0, sizeof(*evhost_stats));
3444 evhost_stats->transport_handle = iscsi_handle(transport);
3445 evhost_stats->type = nlh->nlmsg_type;
3446 evhost_stats->u.get_host_stats.host_no =
3447 ev->u.get_host_stats.host_no;
3448 buf = (char *)evhost_stats + sizeof(*evhost_stats);
3449 memset(buf, 0, host_stats_size);
3450
3451 err = transport->get_host_stats(shost, buf, host_stats_size);
3452 if (err) {
3453 kfree_skb(skbhost_stats);
3454 goto exit_host_stats;
3455 }
3456
3457 actual_size = nlmsg_total_size(sizeof(*ev) + host_stats_size);
3458 skb_trim(skbhost_stats, NLMSG_ALIGN(actual_size));
3459 nlhhost_stats->nlmsg_len = actual_size;
3460
3461 err = iscsi_multicast_skb(skbhost_stats, ISCSI_NL_GRP_ISCSID,
3462 GFP_KERNEL);
3463 } while (err < 0 && err != -ECONNREFUSED);
3464
3465exit_host_stats:
3466 scsi_host_put(shost);
3467 return err;
3468}

3470
3471static int
3472iscsi_if_recv_msg(struct sk_buff *skb, struct nlmsghdr *nlh, uint32_t *group)
3473{
3474 int err = 0;
3475 u32 portid;
3476 struct iscsi_uevent *ev = nlmsg_data(nlh);
3477 struct iscsi_transport *transport = NULL;
3478 struct iscsi_internal *priv;
3479 struct iscsi_cls_session *session;
3480 struct iscsi_cls_conn *conn;
3481 struct iscsi_endpoint *ep = NULL;
3482
3483 if (nlh->nlmsg_type == ISCSI_UEVENT_PATH_UPDATE)
3484 *group = ISCSI_NL_GRP_UIP;
3485 else
3486 *group = ISCSI_NL_GRP_ISCSID;
3487
3488 priv = iscsi_if_transport_lookup(iscsi_ptr(ev->transport_handle));
3489 if (!priv)
3490 return -EINVAL;
3491 transport = priv->iscsi_transport;
3492
3493 if (!try_module_get(transport->owner))
3494 return -EINVAL;
3495
3496 portid = NETLINK_CB(skb).portid;
3497
3498 switch (nlh->nlmsg_type) {
3499 case ISCSI_UEVENT_CREATE_SESSION:
3500 err = iscsi_if_create_session(priv, ep, ev,
3501 portid,
3502 ev->u.c_session.initial_cmdsn,
3503 ev->u.c_session.cmds_max,
3504 ev->u.c_session.queue_depth);
3505 break;
3506 case ISCSI_UEVENT_CREATE_BOUND_SESSION:
3507 ep = iscsi_lookup_endpoint(ev->u.c_bound_session.ep_handle);
3508 if (!ep) {
3509 err = -EINVAL;
3510 break;
3511 }
3512
3513 err = iscsi_if_create_session(priv, ep, ev,
3514 portid,
3515 ev->u.c_bound_session.initial_cmdsn,
3516 ev->u.c_bound_session.cmds_max,
3517 ev->u.c_bound_session.queue_depth);
3518 break;
3519 case ISCSI_UEVENT_DESTROY_SESSION:
3520 session = iscsi_session_lookup(ev->u.d_session.sid);
3521 if (session)
3522 transport->destroy_session(session);
3523 else
3524 err = -EINVAL;
3525 break;
3526 case ISCSI_UEVENT_UNBIND_SESSION:
3527 session = iscsi_session_lookup(ev->u.d_session.sid);
3528 if (session)
3529 scsi_queue_work(iscsi_session_to_shost(session),
3530 &session->unbind_work);
3531 else
3532 err = -EINVAL;
3533 break;
3534 case ISCSI_UEVENT_CREATE_CONN:
3535 err = iscsi_if_create_conn(transport, ev);
3536 break;
3537 case ISCSI_UEVENT_DESTROY_CONN:
3538 err = iscsi_if_destroy_conn(transport, ev);
3539 break;
3540 case ISCSI_UEVENT_BIND_CONN:
3541 session = iscsi_session_lookup(ev->u.b_conn.sid);
3542 conn = iscsi_conn_lookup(ev->u.b_conn.sid, ev->u.b_conn.cid);
3543
3544 if (conn && conn->ep)
3545 iscsi_if_ep_disconnect(transport, conn->ep->id);
3546
3547 if (!session || !conn) {
3548 err = -EINVAL;
3549 break;
3550 }
3551
3552 ev->r.retcode = transport->bind_conn(session, conn,
3553 ev->u.b_conn.transport_eph,
3554 ev->u.b_conn.is_leading);
3555 if (ev->r.retcode || !transport->ep_connect)
3556 break;
3557
3558 ep = iscsi_lookup_endpoint(ev->u.b_conn.transport_eph);
3559 if (ep) {
3560 ep->conn = conn;
3561
3562 mutex_lock(&conn->ep_mutex);
3563 conn->ep = ep;
3564 mutex_unlock(&conn->ep_mutex);
3565 } else
3566 iscsi_cls_conn_printk(KERN_ERR, conn,
3567 "Could not set ep conn "
3568 "binding\n");
3569 break;
3570 case ISCSI_UEVENT_SET_PARAM:
3571 err = iscsi_set_param(transport, ev);
3572 break;
3573 case ISCSI_UEVENT_START_CONN:
3574 conn = iscsi_conn_lookup(ev->u.start_conn.sid, ev->u.start_conn.cid);
3575 if (conn)
3576 ev->r.retcode = transport->start_conn(conn);
3577 else
3578 err = -EINVAL;
3579 break;
3580 case ISCSI_UEVENT_STOP_CONN:
3581 conn = iscsi_conn_lookup(ev->u.stop_conn.sid, ev->u.stop_conn.cid);
3582 if (conn)
3583 transport->stop_conn(conn, ev->u.stop_conn.flag);
3584 else
3585 err = -EINVAL;
3586 break;
3587 case ISCSI_UEVENT_SEND_PDU:
3588 conn = iscsi_conn_lookup(ev->u.send_pdu.sid, ev->u.send_pdu.cid);
3589 if (conn)
3590 ev->r.retcode = transport->send_pdu(conn,
3591 (struct iscsi_hdr*)((char*)ev + sizeof(*ev)),
3592 (char*)ev + sizeof(*ev) + ev->u.send_pdu.hdr_size,
3593 ev->u.send_pdu.data_size);
3594 else
3595 err = -EINVAL;
3596 break;
3597 case ISCSI_UEVENT_GET_STATS:
3598 err = iscsi_if_get_stats(transport, nlh);
3599 break;
3600 case ISCSI_UEVENT_TRANSPORT_EP_CONNECT:
3601 case ISCSI_UEVENT_TRANSPORT_EP_POLL:
3602 case ISCSI_UEVENT_TRANSPORT_EP_DISCONNECT:
3603 case ISCSI_UEVENT_TRANSPORT_EP_CONNECT_THROUGH_HOST:
3604 err = iscsi_if_transport_ep(transport, ev, nlh->nlmsg_type);
3605 break;
3606 case ISCSI_UEVENT_TGT_DSCVR:
3607 err = iscsi_tgt_dscvr(transport, ev);
3608 break;
3609 case ISCSI_UEVENT_SET_HOST_PARAM:
3610 err = iscsi_set_host_param(transport, ev);
3611 break;
3612 case ISCSI_UEVENT_PATH_UPDATE:
3613 err = iscsi_set_path(transport, ev);
3614 break;
3615 case ISCSI_UEVENT_SET_IFACE_PARAMS:
3616 err = iscsi_set_iface_params(transport, ev,
3617 nlmsg_attrlen(nlh, sizeof(*ev)));
3618 break;
3619 case ISCSI_UEVENT_PING:
3620 err = iscsi_send_ping(transport, ev);
3621 break;
3622 case ISCSI_UEVENT_GET_CHAP:
3623 err = iscsi_get_chap(transport, nlh);
3624 break;
3625 case ISCSI_UEVENT_DELETE_CHAP:
3626 err = iscsi_delete_chap(transport, ev);
3627 break;
3628 case ISCSI_UEVENT_SET_FLASHNODE_PARAMS:
3629 err = iscsi_set_flashnode_param(transport, ev,
3630 nlmsg_attrlen(nlh,
3631 sizeof(*ev)));
3632 break;
3633 case ISCSI_UEVENT_NEW_FLASHNODE:
3634 err = iscsi_new_flashnode(transport, ev,
3635 nlmsg_attrlen(nlh, sizeof(*ev)));
3636 break;
3637 case ISCSI_UEVENT_DEL_FLASHNODE:
3638 err = iscsi_del_flashnode(transport, ev);
3639 break;
3640 case ISCSI_UEVENT_LOGIN_FLASHNODE:
3641 err = iscsi_login_flashnode(transport, ev);
3642 break;
3643 case ISCSI_UEVENT_LOGOUT_FLASHNODE:
3644 err = iscsi_logout_flashnode(transport, ev);
3645 break;
3646 case ISCSI_UEVENT_LOGOUT_FLASHNODE_SID:
3647 err = iscsi_logout_flashnode_sid(transport, ev);
3648 break;
3649 case ISCSI_UEVENT_SET_CHAP:
3650 err = iscsi_set_chap(transport, ev,
3651 nlmsg_attrlen(nlh, sizeof(*ev)));
3652 break;
3653 case ISCSI_UEVENT_GET_HOST_STATS:
3654 err = iscsi_get_host_stats(transport, nlh);
3655 break;
3656 default:
3657 err = -ENOSYS;
3658 break;
3659 }
3660
3661 module_put(transport->owner);
3662 return err;
3663}
3664
3665/*
3666 * Get message from skb. Each message is processed by iscsi_if_recv_msg.
3667 * Malformed skbs with wrong lengths or invalid creds are not processed.
3668 */
3669static void
3670iscsi_if_rx(struct sk_buff *skb)
3671{
3672 u32 portid = NETLINK_CB(skb).portid;
3673
3674 mutex_lock(&rx_queue_mutex);
3675 while (skb->len >= NLMSG_HDRLEN) {
3676 int err;
3677 uint32_t rlen;
3678 struct nlmsghdr *nlh;
3679 struct iscsi_uevent *ev;
3680 uint32_t group;
3681
3682 nlh = nlmsg_hdr(skb);
3683 if (nlh->nlmsg_len < sizeof(*nlh) + sizeof(*ev) ||
3684 skb->len < nlh->nlmsg_len) {
3685 break;
3686 }
3687
3688 ev = nlmsg_data(nlh);
3689 rlen = NLMSG_ALIGN(nlh->nlmsg_len);
3690 if (rlen > skb->len)
3691 rlen = skb->len;
3692
3693 err = iscsi_if_recv_msg(skb, nlh, &group);
3694 if (err) {
3695 ev->type = ISCSI_KEVENT_IF_ERROR;
3696 ev->iferror = err;
3697 }
3698 do {
3699 /*
3700 * special case for GET_STATS:
3701 * on success - sending reply and stats from
3702 * inside of if_recv_msg(),
3703 * on error - fall through.
3704 */
3705 if (ev->type == ISCSI_UEVENT_GET_STATS && !err)
3706 break;
3707 if (ev->type == ISCSI_UEVENT_GET_CHAP && !err)
3708 break;
3709 err = iscsi_if_send_reply(portid, nlh->nlmsg_type,
3710 ev, sizeof(*ev));
3711 } while (err < 0 && err != -ECONNREFUSED && err != -ESRCH);
3712 skb_pull(skb, rlen);
3713 }
3714 mutex_unlock(&rx_queue_mutex);
3715}

4284/* convert iscsi_port_speed values to ascii string name */
4285static const struct {
4286 enum iscsi_port_speed value;
4287 char *name;
4288} iscsi_port_speed_names[] = {
4289 {ISCSI_PORT_SPEED_UNKNOWN, "Unknown" },
4290 {ISCSI_PORT_SPEED_10MBPS, "10 Mbps" },
4291 {ISCSI_PORT_SPEED_100MBPS, "100 Mbps" },
4292 {ISCSI_PORT_SPEED_1GBPS, "1 Gbps" },
4293 {ISCSI_PORT_SPEED_10GBPS, "10 Gbps" },
4294 {ISCSI_PORT_SPEED_25GBPS, "25 Gbps" },
4295 {ISCSI_PORT_SPEED_40GBPS, "40 Gbps" },
4296};
4297
4298char *iscsi_get_port_speed_name(struct Scsi_Host *shost)
4299{
4300 int i;
4301 char *speed = "Unknown!";
4302 struct iscsi_cls_host *ihost = shost->shost_data;
4303 uint32_t port_speed = ihost->port_speed;
4304
4305 for (i = 0; i < ARRAY_SIZE(iscsi_port_speed_names); i++) {
4306 if (iscsi_port_speed_names[i].value & port_speed) {
4307 speed = iscsi_port_speed_names[i].name;
4308 break;
4309 }
4310 }
4311 return speed;
4312}
4313EXPORT_SYMBOL_GPL(iscsi_get_port_speed_name);

4341static int iscsi_session_match(struct attribute_container *cont,
4342 struct device *dev)
4343{
4344 struct iscsi_cls_session *session;
4345 struct Scsi_Host *shost;
4346 struct iscsi_internal *priv;
4347
4348 if (!iscsi_is_session_dev(dev))
4349 return 0;
4350
4351 session = iscsi_dev_to_session(dev);
4352 shost = iscsi_session_to_shost(session);
4353 if (!shost->transportt)
4354 return 0;
4355
4356 priv = to_iscsi_internal(shost->transportt);
4357 if (priv->session_cont.ac.class != &iscsi_session_class.class)
4358 return 0;
4359
4360 return &priv->session_cont.ac == cont;
4361}

4363static int iscsi_conn_match(struct attribute_container *cont,
4364 struct device *dev)
4365{
4366 struct iscsi_cls_session *session;
4367 struct iscsi_cls_conn *conn;
4368 struct Scsi_Host *shost;
4369 struct iscsi_internal *priv;
4370
4371 if (!iscsi_is_conn_dev(dev))
4372 return 0;
4373
4374 conn = iscsi_dev_to_conn(dev);
4375 session = iscsi_dev_to_session(conn->dev.parent);
4376 shost = iscsi_session_to_shost(session);
4377
4378 if (!shost->transportt)
4379 return 0;
4380
4381 priv = to_iscsi_internal(shost->transportt);
4382 if (priv->conn_cont.ac.class != &iscsi_connection_class.class)
4383 return 0;
4384
4385 return &priv->conn_cont.ac == cont;
4386}
4387
4388static int iscsi_host_match(struct attribute_container *cont,
4389 struct device *dev)
4390{
4391 struct Scsi_Host *shost;
4392 struct iscsi_internal *priv;
4393
4394 if (!scsi_is_host_device(dev))
4395 return 0;
4396
4397 shost = dev_to_shost(dev);
4398 if (!shost->transportt ||
4399 shost->transportt->host_attrs.ac.class != &iscsi_host_class.class)
4400 return 0;
4401
4402 priv = to_iscsi_internal(shost->transportt);
4403 return &priv->t.host_attrs.ac == cont;
4404}
4405
4406struct scsi_transport_template *
4407iscsi_register_transport(struct iscsi_transport *tt)
4408{
4409 struct iscsi_internal *priv;
4410 unsigned long flags;
4411 int err;
4412
4413 BUG_ON(!tt);
4414
4415 priv = iscsi_if_transport_lookup(tt);
4416 if (priv)
4417 return NULL;
4418
4419 priv = kzalloc(sizeof(*priv), GFP_KERNEL);
4420 if (!priv)
4421 return NULL;
4422 INIT_LIST_HEAD(&priv->list);
4423 priv->iscsi_transport = tt;
4424 priv->t.user_scan = iscsi_user_scan;
4425 priv->t.create_work_queue = 1;
4426
4427 priv->dev.class = &iscsi_transport_class;
4428 dev_set_name(&priv->dev, "%s", tt->name);
4429 err = device_register(&priv->dev);
4430 if (err)
4431 goto free_priv;
4432
4433 err = sysfs_create_group(&priv->dev.kobj, &iscsi_transport_group);
4434 if (err)
4435 goto unregister_dev;
4436
4437 /* host parameters */
4438 priv->t.host_attrs.ac.class = &iscsi_host_class.class;
4439 priv->t.host_attrs.ac.match = iscsi_host_match;
4440 priv->t.host_attrs.ac.grp = &iscsi_host_group;
4441 priv->t.host_size = sizeof(struct iscsi_cls_host);
4442 transport_container_register(&priv->t.host_attrs);
4443
4444 /* connection parameters */
4445 priv->conn_cont.ac.class = &iscsi_connection_class.class;
4446 priv->conn_cont.ac.match = iscsi_conn_match;
4447 priv->conn_cont.ac.grp = &iscsi_conn_group;
4448 transport_container_register(&priv->conn_cont);
4449
4450 /* session parameters */
4451 priv->session_cont.ac.class = &iscsi_session_class.class;
4452 priv->session_cont.ac.match = iscsi_session_match;
4453 priv->session_cont.ac.grp = &iscsi_session_group;
4454 transport_container_register(&priv->session_cont);
4455
4456 spin_lock_irqsave(&iscsi_transport_lock, flags);
4457 list_add(&priv->list, &iscsi_transports);
4458 spin_unlock_irqrestore(&iscsi_transport_lock, flags);
4459
4460 printk(KERN_NOTICE "iscsi: registered transport (%s)\n", tt->name);
4461 return &priv->t;
4462
4463unregister_dev:
4464 device_unregister(&priv->dev);
4465 return NULL;
4466free_priv:
4467 kfree(priv);
4468 return NULL;
4469}
4470EXPORT_SYMBOL_GPL(iscsi_register_transport);
4471
4472int iscsi_unregister_transport(struct iscsi_transport *tt)
4473{
4474 struct iscsi_internal *priv;
4475 unsigned long flags;
4476
4477 BUG_ON(!tt);
4478
4479 mutex_lock(&rx_queue_mutex);
4480
4481 priv = iscsi_if_transport_lookup(tt);
4482 BUG_ON (!priv);
4483
4484 spin_lock_irqsave(&iscsi_transport_lock, flags);
4485 list_del(&priv->list);
4486 spin_unlock_irqrestore(&iscsi_transport_lock, flags);
4487
4488 transport_container_unregister(&priv->conn_cont);
4489 transport_container_unregister(&priv->session_cont);
4490 transport_container_unregister(&priv->t.host_attrs);
4491
4492 sysfs_remove_group(&priv->dev.kobj, &iscsi_transport_group);
4493 device_unregister(&priv->dev);
4494 mutex_unlock(&rx_queue_mutex);
4495
4496 return 0;
4497}
4498EXPORT_SYMBOL_GPL(iscsi_unregister_transport);

4500static __init int iscsi_transport_init(void)
4501{
4502 int err;
4503 struct netlink_kernel_cfg cfg = {
4504 .groups = 1,
4505 .input = iscsi_if_rx,
4506 };
4507 printk(KERN_INFO "Loading iSCSI transport class v%s.\n",
4508 ISCSI_TRANSPORT_VERSION);
4509
4510 atomic_set(&iscsi_session_nr, 0);
4511
4512 err = class_register(&iscsi_transport_class);
4513 if (err)
4514 return err;
4515
4516 err = class_register(&iscsi_endpoint_class);
4517 if (err)
4518 goto unregister_transport_class;
4519
4520 err = class_register(&iscsi_iface_class);
4521 if (err)
4522 goto unregister_endpoint_class;
4523
4524 err = transport_class_register(&iscsi_host_class);
4525 if (err)
4526 goto unregister_iface_class;
4527
4528 err = transport_class_register(&iscsi_connection_class);
4529 if (err)
4530 goto unregister_host_class;
4531
4532 err = transport_class_register(&iscsi_session_class);
4533 if (err)
4534 goto unregister_conn_class;
4535
4536 err = bus_register(&iscsi_flashnode_bus);
4537 if (err)
4538 goto unregister_session_class;
4539
4540 nls = netlink_kernel_create(&init_net, NETLINK_ISCSI, &cfg);
4541 if (!nls) {
4542 err = -ENOBUFS;
4543 goto unregister_flashnode_bus;
4544 }
4545
4546 iscsi_eh_timer_workq = create_singlethread_workqueue("iscsi_eh");
4547 if (!iscsi_eh_timer_workq) {
4548 err = -ENOMEM;
4549 goto release_nls;
4550 }
4551
4552 return 0;
4553
4554release_nls:
4555 netlink_kernel_release(nls);
4556unregister_flashnode_bus:
4557 bus_unregister(&iscsi_flashnode_bus);
4558unregister_session_class:
4559 transport_class_unregister(&iscsi_session_class);
4560unregister_conn_class:
4561 transport_class_unregister(&iscsi_connection_class);
4562unregister_host_class:
4563 transport_class_unregister(&iscsi_host_class);
4564unregister_iface_class:
4565 class_unregister(&iscsi_iface_class);
4566unregister_endpoint_class:
4567 class_unregister(&iscsi_endpoint_class);
4568unregister_transport_class:
4569 class_unregister(&iscsi_transport_class);
4570 return err;
4571}
4572
4573static void __exit iscsi_transport_exit(void)
4574{
4575 destroy_workqueue(iscsi_eh_timer_workq);
4576 netlink_kernel_release(nls);
4577 bus_unregister(&iscsi_flashnode_bus);
4578 transport_class_unregister(&iscsi_connection_class);
4579 transport_class_unregister(&iscsi_session_class);
4580 transport_class_unregister(&iscsi_host_class);
4581 class_unregister(&iscsi_endpoint_class);
4582 class_unregister(&iscsi_iface_class);
4583 class_unregister(&iscsi_transport_class);
4584}

4586module_init(iscsi_transport_init);
4587module_exit(iscsi_transport_exit);
